🔷 ☕ Java 17 (2021) — Enterprise Stability + Cleaner Code (LTS)

🚩 Problems after Java 8

-Still too much boilerplate (getters/setters)
-Hard to model restricted hierarchies
-Pattern matching was weak

Needed long-term stable version

🔑 What Java 17 introduced (deep understanding)

1. Records (Boilerplate Killer)

record User(String name, int age) {}

👉 Automatically gives:

-Constructor
-Getters
-toString(), equals(), hashCode()

👉 Why important:

a.Reduces 50–70% code in DTOs
b.Makes code more readable

2. Sealed Classes (Controlled Inheritance)

sealed class Shape permits Circle, Square {}

👉 Only specific classes can extend it

👉 Why important:

(i)Prevents misuse of inheritance
(ii)Useful in domain modeling

3. Pattern Matching for instanceof

Before:

if (obj instanceof String) {
    String s = (String) obj;
}

After:

if (obj instanceof String s) {
}

👉 Why important:

(i)Less casting
(ii)Cleaner logic

4. Improved Switch

int result = switch(day) {
    case MONDAY -> 1;
    default -> 0;
};

👉 No fall-through bugs

5. JVM & GC Improvements

-Better memory usage
-Faster execution


🔄 Improvement over Java 8

👉 Java 8 made coding easier
👉 Java 17 made coding clean, safe, and production-ready

✅ Final Impact

👉 Java 17 became:

a. Industry standard (LTS)
